        "client_msg_id": "18a1b447-ab73-4c4c-9628-c47e5e20989c",
        "text": "I was thinking about that too yesterday.  There are _definitely_ some (rare, but it is all software) episodes where parts of CRAN bite each other.  Another example is the woes Matrix and lme4 had with each other's upgrades a while back.  And ... some packages do not catch up, remain borked for a bit and then get removed by CRAN.\n\nSo while the \"CRAN guaranty\" generally holds, it is a wee bit relative too as we all know that there is not such thing as perfect certainties.\n\nAnyway, I also wanted to add that sometimes when I have to \/ need to 'freeze' something to be perfectly reliable I also stick it into a Docker container, or sometimes for R, into a 'tucked-away-to-the-side' path that I opt-in.  I.e. I keep an ancient version of `roxygen2` for simple packages where I don't want it to decide it needs to rebuild the package.",
        "team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "user_team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "source_team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
