                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " some (rare, but it is all software) episodes where parts of CRAN bite each other.  Another example is the woes Matrix and lme4 had with each other's upgrades a while back.  And ... some packages do not catch up, remain borked for a bit and then get removed by CRAN.\n\nSo while the \"CRAN guaranty\" generally holds, it is a wee bit relative too as we all know that there is not such thing as perfect certainties.\n\nAnyway, I also wanted to add that sometimes when I have to \/ need to 'freeze' something to be perfectly reliable I also stick it into a Docker container, or sometimes for R, into a 'tucked-away-to-the-side' path that I opt-in.  I.e. I keep an ancient version of "
